<br>
As far as suing just for the sake of money, I'd have to say that losing your job because of something that wasn't your fault and having ridiculously expensive car and medical bills as well as personal anguish and mental stress is not exactly &quot;for the sake of money.&quot;<br>
<br>
You are suing for the sake of equilibrium in your life, and the world in general. Sure, it was an accident and forgiveness is noble, but forgiving for an accident occuring that was precipitated by outside circumstances doesn't exculpate those responsible. <br>
<br>
You aren't getting revenge, you are attempting to resume or maintain a previous balance.<br>
